First factor everything:

\[
\frac{t^{2}-4t-12}{t^{2}+8t+12}
\;=\;
\frac{(t-6)(t+2)}{(t+6)(t+2)},
\qquad
\frac{t^{2}-36}{6t}
\;=\;
\frac{(t-6)(t+6)}{6t}.
\]

So

\[
\frac{t^{2}-4t-12}{t^{2}+8t+12}\;\div\;\frac{t^{2}-36}{6t}
=
\frac{(t-6)(t+2)}{(t+6)(t+2)}
\;\times\;
\frac{6t}{(t-6)(t+6)}.
\]

Cancel common factors \((t-6)\) and \((t+2)\):

\[
=\frac{6t}{(t+6)\,(t+6)}
=\frac{6t}{(t+6)^2}.
\]

Domain restrictions (from all original denominators and from not dividing by zero):  
\(t\neq -6,-2,0,6\).

Answer:
\[
\boxed{\frac{6t}{(t+6)^2},\quad t\neq -6,-2,0,6.}
\]

To subtract, combine over the common denominator and simplify:

\[
\frac{d^2}{d+4}-\frac{3d+28}{d+4}
=\frac{d^2-\bigl(3d+28\bigr)}{d+4}
=\frac{d^2-3d-28}{d+4}
=\frac{(d-7)(d+4)}{d+4}
=d-7,
\]
with the restriction \(d\neq -4\).

First factor \(z^2-49=(z-7)(z+7)\).  Then

Numerator
= \(\displaystyle \frac{2}{(z-7)(z+7)}+\frac1{z+7}
=\frac{2+(z-7)}{(z-7)(z+7)}
=\frac{z-5}{(z-7)(z+7)}.\)

Denominator
= \(\displaystyle \frac9{z+7}+\frac{12}{z-7}
=\frac{9(z-7)+12(z+7)}{(z-7)(z+7)}
=\frac{21(z+1)}{(z-7)(z+7)}.\)

Hence the whole expression is
\[
\frac{\frac{z-5}{(z-7)(z+7)}}{\frac{21(z+1)}{(z-7)(z+7)}}
=\frac{z-5}{21\,(z+1)},
\]
with \(z\neq7,\,-7,\,-1\).
